  "description": "<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>Absalon + Agathe is a short canyoneering route of two adjacent\nravines. This is considered a beginner route, with easy access, small\nrappels, excellent anchors and no major hazards.</p>\n<p>This route is easily accessed and can be done in only a few hours.\nIt's probably a good first canyon to do on Martinique. After rains, flow\nmay be heavier, and the canyon more fun.</p>\n<p>The stream is easily visible on the entire approach, and the canyon\ncan be quickly escaped at most points.</p>\n<h2 id=\"approach\">Approach</h2>\n<p>Park at the old power station. There are several mean-looking\npitbulls here that are chained up 24/7.</p>\n<figure>\n<img src=\"AbsalonAgatheparkinga.jpg\" title=\"Parking area\" width=\"400\" />\n<figcaption>Parking area</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>From the parking lot, head down the steps to the south into the\nravine. This is an excellent trail used by numerous hikers and\nwalkers.</p>\n<p>Follow this main trail for around 15 minutes. You'll have good views\nof the stream and flow levels.</p>\n<figure>\n<img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_trail.jpg\" title=\"The excellent approach trail\"\nwidth=\"400\" />\n<figcaption>The excellent approach trail</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>There is a distinct concrete block on the left of the trail where the\ncanyon starts. It's easy to miss this point. Remember, this canyon's gpx\ntrack was recorded in the forest, and may be slightly off. Use the photo\nbelow.</p>\n<figure>\n<img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_start.jpg\"\ntitle=\"Concrete block that marks the start\" width=\"400\" />\n<figcaption>Concrete block that marks the start</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>This concrete block makes a good place to suit up before starting the\nroute.</p>\n<h2 id=\"descent\">Descent</h2>\n<p>Once in the stream, head downstream. In only a few minutes, you're\narrive at a waterfall into a slot. This is the first rappel.</p>\n<p><img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_r1.jpg\" title=\"The first rappel\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"The first rappel\" /> <img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_slot.jpg\"\ntitle=\"A short section of slot after the first rappel\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"A short section of slot after the first rappel\" /></p>\n<p>The canyon then opens, and there are a few downclimbs and small\nrappels and swims.</p>\n<figure>\n<img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_pool.jpg\" title=\"A nice pool in Absalon\"\nwidth=\"400\" />\n<figcaption>A nice pool in Absalon</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>After this section, on the left is a basic trail cutting up the hill\naway from the stream. Take this trail. This trail goes up to the Agathe\nRavine.</p>\n<p><img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_intersection.jpg\"\ntitle=\"The trail up Agathe starts to the right of the boulder in this photo\"\nwidth=\"400\"\nalt=\"The trail up Agathe starts to the right of the boulder in this photo\" />\n<img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_agathetrail.jpg\" title=\"The trail to Agathe\"\nwidth=\"400\" alt=\"The trail to Agathe\" /></p>\n<p>The trail to Agathe is short, maybe 10-15 minutes. You then arrive at\na small stream which drops off into a stunning slot. This slot is\nnarrow, dark, and rare for Martinique. Rappel in!</p>\n<p><img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_topagather.jpg\"\ntitle=\"The start of the Agathe slot\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"The start of the Agathe slot\" /> <img\nsrc=\"111Absalon_Agathe_r1.jpg\"\ntitle=\"Rappel into the stunning Agathe slot\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"Rappel into the stunning Agathe slot\" /></p>\n<p>Inside this slot, there are several small rappels and downclimbs in\nflowing water.</p>\n<p><img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_insideslot.jpg\" title=\"Inside the slot\"\nwidth=\"400\" alt=\"Inside the slot\" /> <img\nsrc=\"Absalon_Agathe_downclimb.jpg\" title=\"Another drop in Agathe\"\nwidth=\"400\" alt=\"Another drop in Agathe\" /></p>\n<p>The slot opens, all too soon, and you're back at the Absalon stream.\nThe route, unfortunately, is over.</p>\n<h2 id=\"exit\">Exit</h2>\n<p>After descending Agathe, head upriver for just a few minutes, until\njust below the turnoff for the trail up to Agathe that you already\nwalked. On the right-downcanyon bank is a small, steep trail heading up\nthe bank of the creek. Follow this trail up for a few minutes back to\nthe main path along the stream. Follow the main path back to your\ncar.</p>\n<p><img src=\"Absalon_Agathe_path.jpg\"\ntitle=\"Path climbing out from the stream ravine\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"Path climbing out from the stream ravine\" /> <img\nsrc=\"Absalon_Agathe_mainpath.jpg\"\ntitle=\"Main path back to the parking area\" width=\"400\"\nalt=\"Main path back to the parking area\" /></p>\n<h2 id=\"red_tape\">Red tape</h2>\n<p>No red tape.</p>\n<h2 id=\"beta_sites\">Beta sites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_fr.png\" title=\"rwl_fr.png\" alt=\"rwl_fr.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://descente-canyon.com/canyoning/canyon-description/21938\">Descente-Canyon.com</a>\n: Absalon et ravine Agathe</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://icopro.org/canyon/view/id/108\">Icopro.org</a> : Rivi√®re\nAbsalon et ravine Agathe</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_fr.png\" title=\"rwl_fr.png\" alt=\"rwl_fr.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://ankanionla-madinina.com/Martinique/Pitons/Absalon%20ravine%20Agathe.htm?kmlidxna\">An\nKanion La-madinina</a> : Absalon-ravine Agathe</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_fr.png\" title=\"rwl_fr.png\" alt=\"rwl_fr.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://WWW.murdeau-caraibe.com/les-canyons/martinique/absalon-ravine-agathe\">Mur\nd'Eau Caraibe</a> : Absalon Ravine Agathe</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_fr.png\" title=\"rwl_fr.png\" alt=\"rwl_fr.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://ankanionla-madinina.com/Files/Other/Divers/Liste%20rivieres%20et%20ravines.pdf?id=PC-1&amp;kmlidx=14.6705:-61.0948:14.6643:-61.0932\">An\nKanion La-madinina</a> : Absalon - Ravine Agathe [PC-1]</li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"https://www.lukaseddy.com/canyons-of-martinique\">LukasEddy.com</a>\n: Canyons of Martinique</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media</h2>\n<h2 id=\"background\">Background</h2>\n<p>Probably first descended in the 1990s by local canyoneers. Today,\nguided groups occasionally go down it.</p>\n<p>There have been some cases of leptospirosis in this stream. Risk of\ncatching this disease is generally highest after heavy rains. Keep your\ncuts clean, before and after the canyon, and do not drink the water.</p>\n",
